pageContext.claim: “The point is this: health-care – we have it; we have the votes.”
pageContext.analysis: There were not enough votes for Graham-Cassidy, after Sen. Lisa Murkowski (R-Ala.), Sen. Susan Collins (R-Me.) and Sen. Rand Paul (R-Ky.) were not supportive of the measure. It did not make it to a vote because there was not enough Republican support for 50 votes through the reconciliation process.
